  "prompt": "What is average cost per couple to travel Bhutan from AHMEDABAD?",
  "response": "The cost of traveling to Bhutan from Ahmedabad can vary widely based on several factors, including the time of year, travel preferences, and packages chosen. Here\u2019s a rough estimate of the average cost per couple:\n\n1. **Flights**: Round-trip flights from Ahmedabad to Bhutan (Paro) may range from \u20b920,000 to \u20b940,000 per person, depending on the season and how far in advance you book. So, for couples, the cost could range from \u20b940,000 to \u20b980,000.\n\n2. **Tour Package**: Bhutan has a minimum daily spend requirement for tourists, which can be around $200 (about \u20b915,000) per person per day. This fee typically includes accommodation, meals, transportation, and a guide. For a week-long trip, this can amount to approximately \u20b92,10,000 for two.\n\n3. **Additional Expenses**: Consider costs for activities, souvenirs, travel insurance, and other miscellaneous expenses, which might add another \u20b920,000 to \u20b930,000 for the couple.\n\n**Estimated Total**: Adding these costs together, a rough estimate for a week-long trip for a couple could be between \u20b92,70,000 to \u20b93,00,000 or more, depending on preferences and choices.\n\n**Note**: Prices can fluctuate, and it\u2019s advisable to check for updated rates, as well as potential discounts or deals in travel packages.",
